{"name":"Storm of Iron","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"When facing massed enemies on the battlefield, the character lays down a storm of firepower that even the most foolhardy cannot push through. When the character deals Damage to a target with a semi-auto burst or a full-auto burst, the character may allocate his extra hits to any other target within five metres, instead of the usual two metres.","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"2","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"Ballistic Skill 45, Weapon Training (any ranged)","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Ballistic Skill, Offence","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"stormofiron","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"ranged","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"1Hnf3JIYJ2Kswct3"}
{"name":"Disturbing Voice","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"The character&rsquo;s voice has particularly baleful or menacing qualities, causing others to quail before it. The character gains a +10 bonus to all Intimidate Skill Tests, but suffers a -10 penalty to Fellowship Tests when dealing with others in a non-threatening manner, such as animals, children, or the easily startled. In addition, the character is more adept as instilling fear in his followers and when using the Command Terrify Special Skill Use (see page 119), and adds +10 to his Command Skill Test to counter the effects of Fear.","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"1","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"None","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Fellowship, Social","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"disturbingvoice","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"social, fear","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"2iySDXavE8I8X3j1"}
{"name":"Radiant Presence","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"There is something strong and inspiring about the character, the way he holds himself and the look in his eyes, that puts people at ease, filling them with confidence. Everyone within 20 metres that can see the character feels inspired just by being near them and suffers lessened effects from things that would upset or distress them. Those affected gain a +10 to Willpower Tests to resist Fear or against Intimidation attempts. This ability affects all allies close to the character, though not the character himself.","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"1","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"Fellowship 40","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Fellowship, Leadership","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"radiantpresence","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"command, fear","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"62Q1ve3zQjKbtH9r"}
{"name":"Deflect Shot","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"The character&rsquo;s weapons move with such speed that they can deflect thrown weapons and shots fired from primitive weapons. When the character is armed with a readied melee weapon, they add their Weapon Skill Bonus to their Armour Points on all locations (even unarmoured locations) when calculating Damage from hits from ranged weapons with the Primitive Special Quality or Thrown weapons.","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"2","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"Agility 50","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Weapon Skill, Defence","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"deflectshot","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"defence","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"83SD8My9d5UpsYXg"}
{"name":"Arms Master","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"The character is a true master of weapons and there is practically nothing he cannot pick up and use with ease, from autoguns to plasma pistol or chainswords to shock mauls. When the character uses a weapon he is untrained in, he only suffers a -10 penalty, rather than a -20. The only exception to Arms Master are exotic weapons, which are so unusual or rare that they always require their own weapon training Talents to use without penalty, and gain no bonus when combined with this Talent.","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"3","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"Weapon Skill 40, Ballistic Skill 40, Weapon Training (any two)","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Weapon Skill, Ballistic Skill","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"armsmaster","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"combat","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"BfZKE4eUZAOrWGrK"}
{"name":"Master Enginseer","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"The character&rsquo;s knowledge of engines and their machine spirits surpasses all but the most venerable servants of the Machine-God. The character can feel the plasma pulsing through a reactor&rsquo;s conduits as if it was in his own veins. The character gains a +10 bonus on Tech-Use Skill Tests. The character may spend a Fate Point to automatically succeed on a Tech-Use Skill Test for enhancement, repair, or upgrade of a machine&rsquo;s system, taking the minimum amount of time possible on the task. In addition, at the GM&rsquo;s discretion, the character may repair objects without all the parts to hand, jury-rigging a working device as good as the original.","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"3","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"Tech Use +20, Mechanicus Implants","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Intelligence, Tech","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"masterenginseer","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"tech","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"CgLXHu6M9o4TOzt3"}
{"name":"Light Sleeper","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"The slightest change in conditions or disturbance brings the character from sleep to full awareness, remaining alert even in slumber. The character is always assumed to be awake, even when asleep, for the purposes of Awareness Tests or surprise. Unfortunately, the character&rsquo;s sleep is not deep and can be frequently interrupted, resulting in a less-than-cheery disposition when awake.","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"1","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"Perception 30","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Perception, Fieldcraft","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"lightsleeper","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"awareness","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"CyumojmEQAXSxFo9"}
{"name":"Inspire Wrath","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"The character&rsquo;s personal vitriol and bitter hatred is so ingrained in his being that he can inspire the same hate in others. As a Full Action, the character can make a Charm Test to grant the effects of the Hatred Talent to their Squad, or any people in their immediate vicinity. Success on the Test grants the Hatred Talent to the listeners (with the object of hate chosen by the character) for the duration of an encounter. Listeners can resist the effects of the character&rsquo;s speech (and therefore not be burdened with his chosen hatred) by passing an Opposed Willpower Test against the character&rsquo;s Charm Skill Test. Inspire Wrath affects a number of people up to 10 times the character&rsquo;s Fellowship, which can be increased with the use of the Master Orator Talent as normal. Both players and GMs should bear in mind, however, that once a crowd has been inspired to hatred or mindless anger, the effects can be unpredictable and are seldom exactly as the character intends.","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"2","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"Air of Authority","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Fellowship, Leadership","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"inspirewrath","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"command","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"CzN89d4fr5aO4psl"}
{"name":"Orthoproxy","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"Either part of the character&rsquo;s brain has been removed or an inhibitor such as a reason inhibitor circuit has been implanted within the character&rsquo;s skull, allowing him to ignore the mental strain that would affect a more &ldquo;complete&rdquo; person. The character receives a +20 bonus to Willpower Tests made to resist mind control or interrogation. However, he tends not to get jokes.","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"1","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"None","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Willpower, Tech","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"orthproxy","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"social","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"F3Ga2PAhfRXf4Ikc"}
{"name":"Unshakeable Faith","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"The Guardsman&rsquo;s faith in the Emperor and his abilities is so strong that he can face any danger. The character may re-roll any failed Willpower Tests to avoid the effects of Fear.","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"2","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"Willpower 35","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Willpower, Defence","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"unshakeablefaith","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"fear","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"HLruDcl1uukmdk1N"}
{"name":"Polyglot","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"The character has an innate ability to derive meaning from unknown languages and can make himself understood using this intuitive grasp. The character can make untrained Skill Tests with the Linguistics Skill even though it is a Specialist Skill. Being a Polyglot is not the same as having a true knowledge of a language, and characters must make a Linguistics Skill Test (with the -20 for being untrained) to have more than the most basic conversations or exchanges of ideas.","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"1","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"Intelligence 40, Fellowship 30","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Intelligence, Social","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"polyglot","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"social","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"HOJgvFsgrKC9sw5N"}
{"name":"Total Recall","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"Mental conditioning or cranial augmentation enables the character to record and recall great amounts of information, effectively granting them a perfect memory. The character can automatically remember trivial facts or pieces of information the character might feasibly have picked up in the past. When dealing with more detailed, complex, or obscure facts, such as the exact layout of a defence network, the GM may require a successful Intelligence Test to recall the information.","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"1","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"Intelligence 30","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Intelligence, Knowledge","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"totalrecall","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"knowledge","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"IyBcb1YMFy5CuCuH"}
{"name":"Combat Formation","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"The character makes sure the Squad is constantly alert and prepared for danger, planning out their actions for many contingencies if attacked. All members of the Squad (including the character) add +1 to their Initiative rolls. Any member of the Squad may also choose to use the Intelligence Bonus of this character for their Initiative roll rather than their own Agility Bonus.","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"1","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"Intelligence 40","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Leadership, Fieldcraft","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"combatformation","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"initiative","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"JIRgVJClxpUO1vqx"}
{"name":"Foresight","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"Logic and analysis do for the character what animal entrails and the bones claim to do for the superstitious masses. By careful consideration of all the possible consequences and examination of all evidence and information, the character can identify the best path for success. By spending ten minutes studying or analysing a problem, the character gains a +10 bonus to his next Intelligence Test or a Skill Test based on Intelligence.","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"2","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"Intelligence 30","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Intelligence, Knowledge","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"foresight","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"research","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"LvKJvVadrQrJxEQV"}
{"name":"Mimic","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"Vox synthesisers, training, or innate abilities allow the character to accurately mimic the voice of another. For proper imitation, the character must study the voice patterns of their intended target for at least one hour and speak the same language. The character cannot accurately copy the voice of a xenos due to the difference in physiology and the subtle complexities of most alien languages. Listeners must succeed on a Scrutiny Skill Test with a -10 penalty to penetrate the deception. If the character&rsquo;s study used vox recordings or comm-link conversations rather than in-person observation, then there is no penalty to the Scrutiny Skill Test to see through it. The character&rsquo;s deception automatically fails if the listener can clearly see them.","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"1","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"None","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Fellowship, Social","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"mimic","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"social, deceive","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"N0Mp3ZVMeaVxHVxC"}
{"name":"Paranoia","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"The character knows that danger lurks behind every corner and that the galaxy will hit him as soon as he lets his guard down. The character gains a +2 bonus on Initiative rolls and the GM may secretly Test using the character&rsquo;s Perception to notice hidden threats. The price of this eternal vigilance is a twitchy disposition and the inability to relax.","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"2","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"None","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Perception, Fieldcraft","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"paranoia","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"initiative","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"SGeMuyVwjcxJh57e"}
{"name":"Into the Jaws of Hell","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"The character&rsquo;s cool demeanour and faith in the Emperor inspire those around him to great feats. Comrades become immune to the effects of Fear and Pinning as long as they are within 10 metres of him.","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"3","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"Iron Discipline, Fellowship 50","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Fellowship, Leadership","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"intothejawsofhell","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"command","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"VmTneSlGFqBt3tlM"}
{"name":"Cold hearted","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"Either chemical and surgical treatments or sheer will has rendered the character immune to most mundane temptations. Seduction attempts against him automatically fail and Charm Tests increase their Difficulty by one level. Taking this Talent causes one Insanity Point.","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"1","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"None","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Willpower, Defence","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"coldhearted","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"social, defence","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"XNVU4l5KfP7Y1E7q"}
{"name":"Iron Discipline","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"Iron sharpens iron. The character does not coddle his squad- mates nor motivate them through kindness. The character&rsquo;s stalwart example and stern leadership exhorts them with steel instead of praise. If the Player Character fails a Fear or Pinning Test, his Comrade only fails if the roll was a double.","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"2","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"Fellowship 30","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Fellowship, Leadership","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"irondiscipline","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"command","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"ZfRXgDfj5v8sQH9I"}
{"name":"Berserk Charge","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"The character has learned to put the whole force of their momentum behind their weapon blows and when the character charges into combat, few can stand before them. If the character uses the Charge Action, his Weapon Skill Test is Easy (+30) instead of Routine (+20).","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"1","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"None","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Strength, Offence","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"berserkcharge","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"combat","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"fHdVlE30cEiIZjz4"}
{"name":"Medititation","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"The character has mastered their body and its reactions by the practice of meditative techniques, shutting down unnecessary functions and enabling them to refresh both body and mind. Success on a Willpower Test and ten minutes without interruptions removes one level of Fatigue.","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"1","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"None","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Willpower, Knowledge","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"meditation","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"tech","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"oGqDldv2LhYxLWs2"}
{"name":"Lasgun Barrage","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"Through years of practice drills and battlefield experience, the character has become a master of the lasgun. The character can use lasguns of all types to unleash devastating volleys of disciplined fire that can cut down his enemies like the sweep of a scythe. When firing any class of Las weapon on full or semi-auto, the character may score one additional Degree of Success (provided the Test is successful) if he does not take a Move Action in his Turn.","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"3","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"Weapon Training (Las), BS 40","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Ballistic Skill, Offence","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"lasgunbarrage","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"range","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"tR4eoZOk7h1CntCV"}
{"name":"Nerves of Steel","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"Long years on the battlefield enable the character to remain calm as fire impacts all around them. The character may re-roll failed Willpower Tests to avoid or recover from Pinning. In addition, he is seldom impressed by the aggressive displays of his enemies and gains a +10 to Willpower Tests when resisting the effects of enemy Intimidation Skill attempts.","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"2","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"None","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Willpower, Defence","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"nervesofsteel","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"pinning","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"tqvuNHxJ6vEbFoeL"}
{"name":"Air of Authority","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"The character was born to command, either motivating or terrifying those under their charge. When making Command Skill Tests, the character may affect a number of targets equal to 100 times their Fellowship Bonus rather than just 10. If the character is giving an Order to his Squad, the order&rsquo;s range is increased by 100 metres. This Talent has no effect on hostile targets and only affects NPCs.","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"1","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"Fellowship 30","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Fellowship, Leadership","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"airofauthority","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"command","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"wYS22rL59UM5WesS"}
{"name":"Rapid Reaction","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"The character has honed his reactions to a razor&rsquo;s edge, allowing him to act while most stand dumbfounded. When surprised or ambushed, a successful Agility Test allows the character to act normally.","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"2","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"Agility 40","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"Agility, Fieldcraft","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"N/A","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"rapidreaction","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"surprise","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"x25NUhwukIJjcJbO"}
{"name":"Munitorum Influence","permission":{"default":0,"rH1O3GTgaMN2UUme":3},"type":"talentntrait","data":{"description":{"value":"Whether through contacts in the Departmento Munitorum or simple fame amongst the ranks of the Imperial Guard, the character has an easier time acquiring equipment for his Squad. The Squad&rsquo;s Logistics Rating increases by +5. This bonus is permanent, and is not removed even if the character who purchased this Talent is killed or removed from the Squad. Purchasing this Talent costs an additional amount of XP equal to 5 times the Squad&rsquo;s current Logictics Rating.","type":"String"},"tier":{"value":"2","type":"Number"},"prereqs":{"value":"None","type":"String"},"aptitudes":{"value":"General, General","type":"String"},"specialisation":{"value":"X","type":"String"},"flagId":{"value":"munitoruminfluence","type":"String"},"tags":{"value":"logistics","type":"String"}},"flags":{},"img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","effects":[],"_id":"zLlsNVlFdvFlReaa"}
